  "landscaping/edge-hill": {
    heroParagraph: "Premium landscaping in Edge Hill — garden renovation and maintenance for Cairns' most prestigious inner suburb. From restoring overgrown tropical gardens on Collins Avenue Queenslanders to establishing new plantings for renovated properties near the Botanic Gardens, Steady Eco brings the knowledge and equipment.",
    localContext: "<p>Edge Hill gardens set the standard for tropical residential landscaping in Cairns. The suburb's character homes — Queenslanders with deep verandahs, mid-century homes with established gardens, and renovated properties blending old and new — all deserve landscaping that matches the investment. This isn't a suburb where a basic turf-and-mulch job cuts it. Edge Hill homeowners expect tropical gardens with depth, texture, and year-round interest.</p><p>Many established Edge Hill gardens were designed decades ago and have become overgrown, with plants competing for space and light. Garden renovations are in high demand — clearing the overgrowth, redesigning garden beds, improving drainage, and replanting with species that suit today's use of the outdoor space. The Botanic Gardens precinct inspires what's possible with tropical plantings, and Edge Hill residents want that standard in their own yards.</p><p>At just 3km from our Freshwater base, Edge Hill is our closest premium suburb. We know the soils (rich volcanic), the shade conditions (heavy canopy from mature trees), and the species that thrive in Edge Hill's microclimate — which is cooler and more sheltered than the open coastal suburbs. Shade-tolerant species like calatheas, bromeliads, and philodendrons thrive here alongside the classic tropical palette.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does landscaping cost in Edge Hill?", a: "Regular garden maintenance from $80/hr. Garden renovations for Edge Hill properties typically $2,000-$10,000+ depending on scope and size. Full tropical garden redesign and installation quoted per project. Free on-site consultations." },
      { q: "What plants work best in Edge Hill's shaded gardens?", a: "Edge Hill's heavy tree canopy creates more shade than coastal suburbs. Calatheas, bromeliads, philodendrons, peace lilies, and ferns thrive in these conditions. For sunnier spots, heliconias, cordylines, and frangipanis. We select plants based on the specific light and soil conditions in your garden." },
      { q: "Can you renovate an overgrown Edge Hill garden?", a: "Yes — this is one of our specialties in Edge Hill. We clear decades of overgrowth, redesign garden beds, improve drainage, add fresh mulch, and replant with species suited to the conditions. The transformation is usually dramatic and completed in 1-3 days." },
      { q: "Do you provide regular maintenance for Edge Hill gardens?", a: "Yes. Fortnightly or weekly maintenance keeps Edge Hill's tropical gardens looking their best. Hedging, weeding, mulching, seasonal planting, and general garden upkeep. We're only 3km away, so scheduling is easy." }
    ]
  },

