  "tree-removal/freshwater": {
    heroParagraph: "Tree removal in Freshwater — our home suburb. From mature rain trees on Intake Road to overgrown mangoes along Quarantine Road and native species backing onto the Barron Gorge, Steady Eco is just minutes away with tipper truck, chipper, and 7 years of experience.",
    localContext: "<p>Freshwater is where we're based, and we know it better than any other suburb. The area sits at the base of the Barron Gorge — home to the Kuranda Scenic Railway and Skyrail — and the lush tropical vegetation that makes Freshwater beautiful also creates constant tree management needs. Properties along Intake Road, Quarantine Road, and toward Kamerunga have large blocks with established tropical trees, many of which have been growing undisturbed for decades.</p><p>The Freshwater Creek corridor runs through the suburb, and properties near the creek have additional tree challenges — large figs and native species with extensive root systems that affect fences, driveways, and foundations. The wet season brings heavy rainfall from the Barron Gorge catchment, and waterlogged soil combined with high winds makes established trees more vulnerable to failure. After major rain events, storm-damaged trees in Freshwater are some of our fastest callouts — because we're literally around the corner.</p><p>Being based in Freshwater means zero travel time and maximum flexibility. We can quote the same day, schedule quickly, and respond to emergencies faster than anywhere else we service. For Freshwater residents, we're not just a contractor — we're a neighbour.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does tree removal cost in Freshwater?", a: "Small trees from $300-$500. Medium trees (5-10m) $800-$2,500. Large trees near structures $3,000-$8,000+. Being based in Freshwater means no travel costs — you get our best pricing. Free on-site assessment." },
      { q: "How quickly can you respond in Freshwater?", a: "Same day for quotes, often same week for the work. For emergencies — fallen trees, storm damage — we can sometimes be on-site within the hour. Being based in Freshwater gives us the fastest possible response time." },
      { q: "Do you remove trees near Freshwater Creek?", a: "Yes. Creek-side properties have specific challenges — large root systems, waterlogged soil, and proximity to the waterway. We remove trees on your property while being mindful of the creek corridor. If the tree is on council-managed riparian land, different rules apply." },
      { q: "Can you remove trees on properties backing onto Barron Gorge?", a: "We remove trees on your private property. Properties near the Barron Gorge National Park boundary need to respect the park edge. We can assess what's on your land and what's not, and advise accordingly." },
      { q: "Is there a travel charge for Freshwater jobs?", a: "No. Freshwater is our home base — zero travel cost. This means Freshwater residents typically get our most competitive pricing for any given job." }
    ]
  },

  "lawn-mowing/freshwater": {
    heroParagraph: "Lawn mowing in Freshwater — our home suburb. From the larger blocks along Quarantine Road to residential properties near the Freshwater station, we're just around the corner with ride-on mower, push mower, and edging equipment. No travel costs, fastest response in Cairns.",
    localContext: "<p>Freshwater properties range from standard suburban blocks near the Freshwater Connection shopping village to large lifestyle blocks along Quarantine Road and toward Kamerunga. The larger blocks need ride-on mowing — the tropical growth rates in this sheltered, high-rainfall pocket at the base of the range produce some of the fastest lawn growth in the Cairns area. A Freshwater lawn in the wet season can need mowing every week to stay presentable.</p><p>The suburb's scenic character — the Kuranda Scenic Railway, Freshwater Creek, and the range backdrop — attracts homeowners who take pride in their properties. Regular mowing isn't just about grass control here; it's about matching the suburb's leafy, well-maintained character. For the residents near the Freshwater station and along the main roads, a tidy lawn is part of the streetscape.</p><p>Being our home base means Freshwater gets priority scheduling and the fastest turnaround of any suburb. No travel time means we can fit Freshwater jobs into gaps in our schedule and offer our most competitive pricing. Most of our regular Freshwater clients have been with us for years.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does lawn mowing cost in Freshwater?", a: "Standard Freshwater blocks $55-$75 per mow including edging and blowing — our best pricing thanks to zero travel. Larger blocks along Quarantine Road with ride-on mowing $80-$120. We quote per property." },
      { q: "How often should Freshwater lawns be mowed?", a: "Fortnightly year-round at minimum. Weekly in the wet season (Nov-Apr) is ideal — Freshwater's sheltered position at the base of the range gets heavy rainfall, and lawns grow extremely fast. The dry season allows fortnightly or even three-weekly mowing." },
      { q: "Do you offer same-day mowing in Freshwater?", a: "Often, yes. Being based in Freshwater means we can fit local jobs into the schedule at short notice. For regular clients, you get a set day each fortnight. For one-off mows, call 0456 190 202 and we'll usually fit you in within a day or two." },
      { q: "Is Freshwater your cheapest area for mowing?", a: "Yes — zero travel costs mean Freshwater residents get our most competitive pricing. It's also our fastest turnaround for scheduling and our quickest response for any urgent requests." }
    ]
  },

