  "tree-removal/gordonvale": {
    heroParagraph: "Professional tree removal in Gordonvale — sugar cane country at the base of Walsh Pyramid. From massive old mango trees on Draper Road acreage to coconut palms threatening tin roofs in the Gordonvale township, we bring tipper truck, chipper, and 7 years of experience to every job.",
    localContext: "<p>Gordonvale sits 23km south of Cairns at the foot of Walsh Pyramid — Queensland's most famous natural pyramid. The surrounding sugar cane country and large rural-residential blocks mean Gordonvale properties often have significant trees: massive old mangoes from original farm plantings, large eucalypts along fence lines, coconut palms near older homes, and native species in the scrub corridors between cane paddocks. These trees have been growing for decades without professional attention, and when they need removing, they're big jobs.</p><p>In the Gordonvale township itself, the older homes on Norman Street, Gordon Street, and the streets around the Gordonvale State School have established tropical gardens with trees that have outgrown their blocks. Root systems lifting footpaths, heavy limbs over power lines, and storm-damaged trees after the wet season all generate regular demand for removal. The Mulgrave Mill precinct and surrounding commercial areas also need tree management around infrastructure and road corridors.</p><p>Gordonvale is 23km south on the Bruce Highway — about 25 minutes from our Freshwater base. It's well within our regular service area and we know the town and surrounding properties well. Whether it's a single tree in the township or a multi-tree clearing job on a Gordonvale acreage block, we bring the full setup and get it done in one visit.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does tree removal cost in Gordonvale?", a: "Small trees from $300-$500. Medium trees $800-$2,500. Large mature mangoes and eucalypts on Gordonvale acreage $3,000-$8,000+. Acreage properties with multiple trees get better batch rates. Free on-site assessment." },
      { q: "Can you remove large old mango trees in Gordonvale?", a: "Yes. Gordonvale has some enormous mangoes from the original farm era — 15m+ with massive canopies. We section them down carefully, chip all branches on-site, and remove the trunk with the tipper. Stump grinding available." },
      { q: "Do you clear trees on rural blocks near Gordonvale?", a: "Yes. The acreage properties and rural-residential blocks around Gordonvale often need multiple trees removed — for new builds, fence-line clearing, or infrastructure access. We handle batch clearing efficiently with our full equipment setup." },
      { q: "How far is Gordonvale from your base?", a: "23km south on the Bruce Highway — about 25 minutes. Gordonvale is well within our regular service area with no significant travel surcharge." },
      { q: "Do you do storm damage clean-up in Gordonvale?", a: "Yes. The Gordonvale area cops heavy wet season storms, and large established trees are vulnerable. After storm events, call 0456 190 202 and we'll prioritise emergency work — fallen trees on houses, vehicles, driveways, and roads." }
    ]
  },

  "lawn-mowing/gordonvale": {
    heroParagraph: "Lawn mowing in Gordonvale — from large acreage blocks backing onto cane fields to township properties along Norman and Gordon Streets. Ride-on mower for the big blocks, push mower for residential detail. 23km south of our base, no drama on scheduling.",
    localContext: "<p>Gordonvale properties span a wide range — from standard residential blocks in the township to large acreage lifestyle properties on the outskirts backing onto sugar cane paddocks. The acreage blocks are where ride-on mowing really earns its keep: 2,000sqm+ of lawn plus cleared areas that would take half a day with a push mower. Our ride-on handles these efficiently, giving a clean, even cut across flat and gently sloping terrain.</p><p>In the Gordonvale township, the older homes have well-established yards with tropical lawns that grow aggressively in the wet. Norman Street, Gordon Street, and the streets near the school have standard suburban blocks that suit push mowing with detailed edging. Many Gordonvale residents are long-term locals who want reliable, no-fuss lawn maintenance — same day each fortnight, job done properly, property left tidy.</p><p>Gordonvale is on our southern route, 23km from base. We service the town alongside Edmonton and Bentley Park clients, making efficient route days. Regular Gordonvale clients get consistent scheduling and competitive pricing.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does lawn mowing cost in Gordonvale?", a: "Township blocks $60-$80 per mow including edging and blowing. Larger acreage blocks with ride-on mowing $80-$150+. Very large rural properties quoted per job. We include edging and blowing with every visit." },
      { q: "Do you do ride-on mowing on Gordonvale acreage?", a: "Yes — that's exactly what the ride-on is for. Gordonvale's larger blocks and cleared acreage properties are ideal for ride-on mowing. What would take 3+ hours with a push mower is done in under an hour." },
      { q: "How often should Gordonvale lawns be mowed?", a: "Fortnightly at minimum. Weekly in the wet season if you want the best presentation. Gordonvale's flat, fertile cane country soil grows grass fast — especially couch and buffalo varieties in the wet." },
      { q: "Do you service the streets near the Gordonvale mill?", a: "Yes — we service all of Gordonvale township and surrounding rural-residential properties. Norman Street, Gordon Street, the school area, and properties along Draper Road and out toward Little Mulgrave are all in our regular service area." }
    ]
  },

