  "lawn-mowing/trinity-beach": {
    heroParagraph: "Regular lawn mowing in Trinity Beach — from beachside units on Vasey Esplanade to family homes along Trinity Beach Road. Ride-on mower for larger blocks, detailed edging every visit. Keeping Trinity Beach lawns sharp for residents, retirees, and holiday rental owners year-round.",
    localContext: "<p>Trinity Beach is one of the Northern Beaches' most popular residential suburbs, and the lawns here reflect that pride of ownership. Families, retirees, and holiday rental investors all need consistent mowing to keep properties looking their best. The beachfront strip along Vasey Esplanade and the streets behind it — Bramston Street, Langley Close, and surrounds — are a mix of well-kept homes and managed holiday rentals where presentation directly affects bookings and property value.</p><p>The tropical climate at Trinity Beach means lawns grow relentlessly in the wet season. Couch, buffalo, and zoysia grasses all thrive in the coastal humidity and heavy rainfall from November through April. Miss a fortnight in January and the lawn is up past your ankles. For holiday rental properties, an overgrown lawn between guests is the fastest way to earn a bad review. Our regular scheduled service keeps Trinity Beach properties looking consistently maintained without the owner needing to lift a finger.</p><p>We service Trinity Beach on our Northern Beaches route — covering Trinity Park, Trinity Beach, Kewarra Beach, and Clifton Beach on the same run. It's 18km north of our Freshwater base, and we're up there weekly. Regular clients get priority scheduling and the same reliable service every visit — mow, edge, blow, done.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does lawn mowing cost in Trinity Beach?", a: "Standard residential blocks in Trinity Beach typically $60-$80 per mow including edging and blowing. Larger properties with ride-on mowing $80-$120. Holiday rental properties on the same schedule as residential clients. We quote per property so you know the cost upfront." },
      { q: "Can you maintain my Trinity Beach holiday rental lawn?", a: "Yes — we maintain lawns for multiple holiday rental properties in Trinity Beach. We mow on a regular fortnightly schedule so the property is always presentable for guests. No need to coordinate around bookings — we just keep it tidy year-round." },
      { q: "How often should lawns be mowed in Trinity Beach?", a: "Fortnightly is the minimum year-round. In the wet season (Nov-Apr), weekly mowing is ideal — the combination of tropical heat, humidity, and heavy rain means grass grows extremely fast. Letting it go 3+ weeks in the wet creates extra work and a rougher finish." },
      { q: "Do you mow the streets behind the Trinity Beach esplanade?", a: "Yes — we service all of Trinity Beach, from the beachfront properties along Vasey Esplanade through to the residential streets behind. Trinity Beach is on our regular Northern Beaches route from Freshwater." },
      { q: "Do you offer ride-on mowing in Trinity Beach?", a: "Yes. For larger Trinity Beach blocks where a push mower would take too long, we bring the ride-on. It gives a cleaner, more even cut on bigger lawn areas and cuts the job time significantly. We also use the push mower for edges and tight spots." }
    ]
  },

  "landscaping/trinity-beach": {
    heroParagraph: "Professional landscaping in Trinity Beach — tropical garden design, renovation, and regular maintenance for families, retirees, and holiday rental owners along the Northern Beaches. From courtyard makeovers to full garden overhauls near Vasey Esplanade, Steady Eco brings 7 years of hands-on experience.",
    localContext: "<p>Trinity Beach has a relaxed coastal character, and the gardens here reflect that — tropical plantings, palm-lined driveways, and colourful flowering hedges are the standard. Properties along the beachfront and the residential streets behind it expect a level of presentation that matches the suburb's reputation as one of Cairns' most liveable beach communities. For holiday rental owners, the garden is the first thing guests see — and first impressions drive reviews.</p><p>The coastal soils at Trinity Beach are sandier than inland suburbs, which affects drainage and plant nutrition. Tropical species like heliconias, frangipanis, crotons, and bird of paradise do well here, but they need proper soil preparation and mulching to establish. Salt-tolerant species are essential for the front-row beachside properties — pandanus, lomandra, and coastal hibiscus handle the salt air without struggling. Irrigation becomes important in the dry season when the sandy soils dry out quickly.</p><p>Many established Trinity Beach homes have gardens that were planted 20-30 years ago and have become overgrown or tired. Garden renovations — clearing old plantings, improving beds, fresh mulch, and replanting with modern tropical species — are one of our most common jobs in Trinity Beach. We also provide regular scheduled maintenance for residents who want their garden looking sharp year-round without doing the work themselves.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does landscaping cost in Trinity Beach?", a: "Regular garden maintenance from $80/hr. Small garden renovations (courtyard, front garden) $500-$1,500. Full property landscaping from $3,000-$10,000+ depending on scope. We provide free on-site quotes for Trinity Beach properties." },
      { q: "What plants work best in Trinity Beach gardens?", a: "Tropical species that handle coastal conditions: frangipanis, heliconias, cordylines, bird of paradise, and bougainvillea. For salt-exposed properties near the beach, pandanus, lomandra, and coastal banksia. We recommend plants based on your garden's specific sun, wind, and salt exposure." },
      { q: "Can you renovate an overgrown Trinity Beach garden?", a: "Yes — this is one of our most common Trinity Beach jobs. We clear overgrown vegetation, chip and remove green waste with our tipper, improve garden beds, add fresh mulch, and replant with species suited to the coastal conditions. Most garden renovations are completed in 1-2 days." },
      { q: "Do you maintain gardens for Trinity Beach holiday rentals?", a: "Yes. We maintain gardens for multiple holiday rental properties in Trinity Beach on regular fortnightly schedules. Hedging, weeding, mulching, and general garden tidy-up ensures your property always looks its best for arriving guests." },
      { q: "Can you install irrigation for a Trinity Beach garden?", a: "We can install basic drip irrigation and garden watering systems for Trinity Beach properties. The sandy coastal soils dry out quickly in the dry season, so irrigation is worth considering for any new planting to help plants establish properly." }
    ]
  },

