  "landscaping/clifton-beach": {
    heroParagraph: "Professional landscaping in Clifton Beach — new garden design for the growing number of modern builds, plus renovation and maintenance for established coastal homes. From new developments off Clifton Road to established properties with ocean views, Steady Eco delivers tropical landscaping that suits Clifton Beach's premium coastal setting.",
    localContext: "<p>Clifton Beach is one of the Northern Beaches' fastest-growing suburbs, and that growth is driving serious demand for landscaping. New developments and modern builds are going up alongside the older established homes, and every new property needs gardens designed and installed from scratch. The ocean-view blocks that Clifton Beach is known for deserve landscaping that complements the outlook — clean tropical plantings, low-maintenance native species, and garden beds that frame the view rather than block it.</p><p>For the established homes in Clifton Beach, many gardens are reaching the point where they need a refresh. Overgrown hedges, tired plantings, and gardens that haven't been redesigned since the house was built are common. The coastal conditions — salt air, sandy soils, strong sea breezes — take a toll on plant species that aren't suited to the environment. A garden renovation with the right salt-tolerant and wind-resistant species makes a massive difference to both presentation and ongoing maintenance effort.</p><p>Clifton Beach sits between Kewarra Beach and Palm Cove, 22km north of our Freshwater base. We service the suburb on our Northern Beaches route and know the local conditions well — the sandy soils, the salt exposure on the ocean-facing blocks, and the tropical species that thrive here. Whether it's establishing a garden on a brand-new build or bringing an older Clifton Beach garden back to life, we bring the equipment and the experience.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does landscaping cost in Clifton Beach?", a: "Garden maintenance from $80/hr. New garden installations for modern builds typically $2,000-$8,000+ depending on size and scope. Garden renovations on established properties $1,000-$5,000. We provide free on-site consultations and written quotes for all Clifton Beach properties." },
      { q: "Can you landscape a new build in Clifton Beach?", a: "Yes — we regularly work on new Clifton Beach properties. We design and install tropical gardens suited to the coastal conditions, including soil preparation, planting, mulching, and garden edging. We work around builder timelines and can start as soon as the site is ready." },
      { q: "What plants handle the salt air at Clifton Beach?", a: "For ocean-facing blocks: pandanus, coastal banksia, lomandra, hibiscus, and bougainvillea all handle salt spray well. For sheltered gardens behind the first row of homes, the full range of tropical species is available — heliconias, frangipanis, cordylines, and bird of paradise." },
      { q: "Do you provide regular garden maintenance in Clifton Beach?", a: "Yes. We offer fortnightly maintenance for Clifton Beach properties — hedging, weeding, mulching, and general garden upkeep. Regular clients get priority scheduling on our Northern Beaches route. Set and forget." },
      { q: "Can you improve drainage in a Clifton Beach garden?", a: "Yes. Clifton Beach's sandy soils generally drain well, but some lower blocks and areas with compacted fill from construction can have drainage issues. We can improve garden bed drainage, redirect runoff, and select plants suited to the specific conditions on your block." }
    ]
  },

  "tree-removal/clifton-beach": {
    heroParagraph: "Professional tree removal in Clifton Beach — from mature palms and poincianas on established properties to site clearing for new builds. 7 years experience, tipper truck, wood chipper, and chainsaws. Clean, careful work that meets Clifton Beach's coastal presentation standards.",
    localContext: "<p>Clifton Beach's mix of new developments and established homes creates two distinct types of tree removal demand. New builds often require clearing of existing vegetation before construction — sometimes mature trees that have been growing undisturbed for decades. Established homes, meanwhile, have coconut palms dropping nuts near pools, poincianas lifting driveways, and mangoes that have outgrown compact coastal blocks. Both situations need professional removal with proper equipment.</p><p>The coastal exposure at Clifton Beach means trees here cop strong sea breezes and occasional cyclonic winds. Coconut palms, she-oaks, and melaleucas are common along the beachfront streets, while further back the standard tropical species — mangoes, poincianas, and rain trees — dominate. After severe weather events, storm-damaged trees need prompt removal to prevent further damage to homes, fences, and cars. Clifton Beach's premium property values mean homeowners don't tolerate hazardous trees lingering.</p><p>We bring our full setup to every Clifton Beach job — tipper truck for immediate waste removal, wood chipper for on-site processing, and chainsaws for controlled sectional removal. For properties with ocean views, removing the right tree can actually open up sightlines and add value. We work carefully around existing gardens, fences, and structures to ensure the removal is clean and the site is left ready for whatever comes next.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does tree removal cost in Clifton Beach?", a: "Small trees under 5m from $300-$500. Medium trees (5-10m) $800-$2,500 depending on access and proximity to structures. Large trees near buildings or power lines $3,000-$8,000+. Free on-site assessment and written quote for every Clifton Beach job." },
      { q: "Can you clear trees for a new build in Clifton Beach?", a: "Yes. We clear vegetation on new Clifton Beach lots — removing selected trees, chipping branches, and leaving the block ready for construction. If council approval is needed for protected species, we can advise on the process before work begins." },
      { q: "Do you remove coconut palms in Clifton Beach?", a: "Yes. Coconut palm removal is common in Clifton Beach — falling coconuts near pools, driveways, and entertaining areas are a safety concern. We remove palms of all sizes, grind the stump, and leave the area clean." },
      { q: "Can you remove a tree to improve ocean views?", a: "If the tree is on your property and not protected, yes. Removing or reducing the right tree can significantly improve ocean views on Clifton Beach blocks. We can assess which trees are candidates for removal and advise on any council requirements." },
      { q: "Do you do emergency tree removal in Clifton Beach after storms?", a: "Yes. Clifton Beach is exposed to coastal storms and cyclones. After severe weather, call 0456 190 202 and we'll respond as fast as possible. Fallen trees on houses, cars, driveways, and fences — we prioritise emergency work." }
    ]
  },

