  "lawn-mowing/kewarra-beach": {
    heroParagraph: "Regular lawn mowing in Kewarra Beach — reliable, consistent service for a suburb that expects premium presentation. From resort-precinct properties to established family homes along Kewarra Street, we keep Kewarra Beach lawns looking sharp every visit.",
    localContext: "<p>Kewarra Beach residents take pride in their properties, and a well-maintained lawn is part of that standard. The suburb's quiet, premium character means overgrown lawns and untidy edges stand out immediately. Whether it's a family home, a retiree's residence, or a resort-managed unit, consistent mowing keeps the property looking its best and the neighbourhood looking cohesive.</p><p>The tropical conditions at Kewarra Beach mean lawns grow fast — especially in the wet season when the combination of coastal humidity, heavy rain, and warm temperatures pushes grass growth to its peak. Couch and buffalo lawns are the most common in Kewarra Beach, and both need regular cutting to stay healthy and presentable. Missing two mows in the wet season means dealing with a lawn that's too long for a clean cut and takes twice the effort to bring back.</p><p>We service Kewarra Beach every fortnight on our Northern Beaches route. It sits between Trinity Beach and Clifton Beach, 20km from our Freshwater base. Every mowing visit includes edging along driveways, paths, and garden beds, plus blowing clean of all clippings. For accommodation properties in the resort precinct, we can schedule around guest arrivals to ensure the property is freshly mowed for every check-in.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does lawn mowing cost in Kewarra Beach?", a: "Standard residential blocks in Kewarra Beach typically $60-$80 per mow including edging and blowing. Larger properties with ride-on mowing $80-$150. Resort and body corporate common areas quoted per site. All prices confirmed upfront before we start." },
      { q: "Can you mow before guests arrive at my Kewarra Beach rental?", a: "Yes. For accommodation and holiday rental properties, we can coordinate mowing around guest arrivals. Most clients prefer a regular fortnightly schedule that keeps the property consistently maintained without needing to time it to bookings." },
      { q: "How often should I mow my Kewarra Beach lawn?", a: "Fortnightly is the minimum year-round. Weekly in the wet season (Nov-Apr) is ideal for the best presentation. In the cooler dry season (May-Oct), fortnightly or even every three weeks is usually sufficient." },
      { q: "Do you edge and blow as part of the mowing service?", a: "Yes — every mowing visit in Kewarra Beach includes edging along driveways, paths, and garden beds, plus blowing all clippings off hard surfaces. It's not an extra — it's part of the standard service. The detail work is what makes the difference." }
    ]
  },

