  "lawn-mowing/bentley-park": {
    heroParagraph: "Regular lawn mowing in Bentley Park — keeping the lawns sharp on one of Cairns' fastest-growing southern suburbs. From new turf on freshly built homes to established blocks along Dalrymple Drive and near the Bentley Park shopping precinct. Ride-on and push mowers, edging and blowing every visit.",
    localContext: "<p>Bentley Park is a modern family suburb, and the homes here are predominantly newer builds on medium-sized blocks. Many properties have turf that's only a few years old and still establishing — regular mowing from early on is essential to develop a thick, healthy lawn. Young families moving into Bentley Park want a neat yard but often don't have the time or equipment to keep up with tropical grass growth, especially once the wet season hits.</p><p>The suburb's layout — clean residential streets, new estates, and a growing commercial precinct — means most blocks are a standard suburban size suited to push mowing with the ride-on available for larger corner blocks and properties with bigger yards. The tropical climate at Bentley Park is the same as the rest of Cairns south — hot, humid, and wet from November through April. Grass grows fast, and skipping a mow quickly turns a tidy lawn into a weekend's hard work.</p><p>We service Bentley Park on our southern route, which covers Edmonton, Bentley Park, Mount Sheridan, and White Rock. It's 13km south of our Freshwater base. Regular Bentley Park clients get the same day each fortnight, consistent service, and a lawn that's always presentation-ready — whether for the family, for sale, or for rental inspection.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does lawn mowing cost in Bentley Park?", a: "Standard Bentley Park residential blocks typically $60-$80 per mow including edging and blowing. Newer estates with smaller yards from $50. Larger blocks with ride-on mowing $80-$120. We quote per property before starting." },
      { q: "How often should I mow a new lawn in Bentley Park?", a: "New turf should be mowed for the first time once it reaches 50-60mm — usually 3-4 weeks after laying. After that, fortnightly year-round with weekly mowing in the wet season (Nov-Apr) to keep it establishing well. Regular mowing promotes thicker, healthier turf." },
      { q: "Do you mow rental properties in Bentley Park?", a: "Yes. We maintain lawns for multiple rental properties in Bentley Park. Regular fortnightly mowing keeps the property presentable for tenants and ready for inspections. We can work with property managers or landlords directly." },
      { q: "Can you handle the wet season growth in Bentley Park?", a: "Yes. We switch many Bentley Park clients to weekly mowing during the wet season when grass growth peaks. Staying on top of it means a cleaner cut every visit and a healthier lawn overall. We adjust schedules seasonally so clients don't need to ask." },
      { q: "Do you service the Bentley Park shopping precinct area?", a: "Yes — we service all of Bentley Park, including the residential streets around the shopping precinct, Dalrymple Drive, and the newer estates. Bentley Park is on our regular southern route." }
    ]
  },

  "landscaping/bentley-park": {
    heroParagraph: "Professional landscaping in Bentley Park — garden design and installation for new homes, plus maintenance and upgrades for established properties. Steady Eco helps Bentley Park families turn builder-basic yards into functional, attractive tropical gardens.",
    localContext: "<p>Bentley Park is full of newer homes where the builder has handed over a basic yard — turf, maybe a few token plants, and bare garden beds. The real landscaping starts after handover, and that's where we come in. Young families in Bentley Park want gardens that look good, are low-maintenance, and can handle kids and pets. Practical tropical plantings — hardy species in mulched beds with clean garden edging — deliver the look without the high-maintenance burden.</p><p>For established Bentley Park homes that are now 10-15 years old, gardens are reaching the point where they need a refresh. Original plantings may have outgrown their space, mulch has broken down, and garden beds need rebuilding. A garden renovation — clearing tired plantings, refreshing beds, adding new mulch and modern tropical species — can transform a tired yard in a day or two.</p><p>We know what works in Bentley Park's conditions. The suburb sits 13km south of Cairns in the same hot, humid tropical belt. Soils are generally good quality from the former agricultural land the suburb was built on. Species like cordylines, lomandras, heliconias, and frangipanis establish quickly and look great with minimal ongoing effort. We design gardens that suit Bentley Park's family-friendly character — practical, attractive, and built to last.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does landscaping cost in Bentley Park?", a: "Garden maintenance from $80/hr. New garden installations for Bentley Park homes — converting builder-basic yards into proper gardens — typically $1,500-$5,000 depending on size and scope. Full property landscaping quoted per project. Free on-site quotes." },
      { q: "Can you landscape a new Bentley Park home after the builder finishes?", a: "Yes — this is one of our most common Bentley Park jobs. Builders leave a basic yard with turf and bare beds. We design and install a complete garden — plants, mulch, garden edging, and any soil improvement needed. We can start as soon as the builder is done." },
      { q: "What low-maintenance plants work in Bentley Park?", a: "Lomandras, cordylines, and agaves for structure. Heliconias and bird of paradise for tropical colour. Frangipanis as feature trees. Crotons and bromeliads for garden bed fill. All are low-maintenance, handle the tropical climate, and look great year-round with minimal effort." },
      { q: "Do you offer regular garden maintenance in Bentley Park?", a: "Yes. Fortnightly garden maintenance for Bentley Park properties — hedging, weeding, mulching, and general garden upkeep. Regular clients get priority scheduling on our southern route. Consistent service, no surprises." },
      { q: "Can you add garden edging to my Bentley Park property?", a: "Yes. Clean garden edging — timber, steel, or concrete — defines garden beds and keeps mulch contained. It's one of the simplest upgrades that makes the biggest visual difference on newer Bentley Park properties." }
    ]
  },

