  "lawn-mowing/mount-sheridan": {
    heroParagraph: "Regular lawn mowing in Mount Sheridan — from large elevated blocks with views to body corporate common areas near Mount Sheridan Plaza. Ride-on mower for the bigger properties, detailed edging on every visit. Serving one of Cairns' largest southern suburbs.",
    localContext: "<p>Mount Sheridan is a major residential suburb south of Cairns, and the mowing demand here is consistent and high. The suburb has a wide mix of properties — large family homes on elevated blocks with views, townhouse complexes with shared lawns, and body corporate developments around the Mount Sheridan Plaza shopping precinct that need regular commercial maintenance. Our ride-on mower handles the larger Mount Sheridan blocks that would take hours with a push mower, while the push mower handles detail work on edges and smaller sections.</p><p>The elevated position of many Mount Sheridan blocks means they're more exposed to wind and sun than lower-lying suburbs, which can affect grass health in the dry season. But in the wet season, the same blocks get hammered with tropical rain and the grass grows as fast as anywhere in Cairns. Consistent mowing through the wet keeps Mount Sheridan lawns healthy — letting them get too long between cuts stresses the grass and creates thatch problems.</p><p>We service Mount Sheridan on our southern route, 11km from our Freshwater base. The suburb is large enough that we have multiple clients on the same streets, which means efficient scheduling and reliable same-day service. For body corporate and strata properties near the plaza, we provide commercial mowing contracts with regular scheduled visits.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does lawn mowing cost in Mount Sheridan?", a: "Standard Mount Sheridan residential blocks $60-$80 per mow including edging and blowing. Larger elevated blocks with ride-on mowing $80-$150. Body corporate and commercial mowing quoted per site. All prices confirmed before we start." },
      { q: "Do you mow body corporate properties in Mount Sheridan?", a: "Yes. We maintain common areas and shared lawns for body corporate and strata properties throughout Mount Sheridan, including developments near Mount Sheridan Plaza. Regular scheduled maintenance on weekly or fortnightly cycles." },
      { q: "Can you handle the large blocks in Mount Sheridan?", a: "Yes. Many Mount Sheridan properties have larger-than-average blocks, especially the elevated ones with views. Our ride-on mower makes quick work of these — a job that would take 2+ hours with a push mower is done in well under an hour." },
      { q: "How often should Mount Sheridan lawns be mowed?", a: "Fortnightly year-round at minimum. Weekly in the wet season (Nov-Apr) for the best results. Mount Sheridan's exposed, elevated blocks dry out faster in the dry season — a slightly longer cut height helps protect the lawn during those drier months." },
      { q: "Do you service all of Mount Sheridan or just certain streets?", a: "We service all of Mount Sheridan — from the elevated blocks up near the mountain to the streets around the plaza and the areas bordering Bentley Park and White Rock. It's one of our busiest southern suburbs." }
    ]
  },

  "tree-removal/mount-sheridan": {
    heroParagraph: "Professional tree removal in Mount Sheridan — from mature trees on large elevated blocks to problematic palms near body corporate complexes around Mount Sheridan Plaza. 7 years experience, tipper truck, wood chipper, and chainsaws. Complete clean-up on every job.",
    localContext: "<p>Mount Sheridan's established properties have mature tropical trees that have been growing for 20-30 years, and many have reached a size where they need professional attention. Large mangoes shading entire yards, poincianas with root systems lifting driveways, and coconut palms dropping nuts onto cars and footpaths are all common removal requests. The elevated blocks in Mount Sheridan often have trees that are more exposed to wind, making them more susceptible to storm damage — and when a large tree fails on a hillside block, it can cause serious damage to the property below.</p><p>The body corporate complexes and townhouse developments around Mount Sheridan Plaza have their own tree management needs. Trees in shared common areas that have outgrown their planting, are interfering with buildings or infrastructure, or have become hazardous after storms all need professional removal. We work with body corporate managers and strata committees to plan and execute tree removal with minimal disruption to residents.</p><p>Mount Sheridan is 11km south of our Freshwater base, and we service the suburb regularly. We bring the full setup — tipper truck for immediate waste removal, wood chipper for on-site processing, and the right chainsaws for the job. For the larger trees on elevated blocks, we use controlled sectional removal to bring the tree down safely in stages, protecting the property and neighbouring homes.</p>",
    faqs: [
      { q: "How much does tree removal cost in Mount Sheridan?", a: "Small trees under 5m from $300-$500. Medium trees (5-10m) between $800-$2,500. Large mature trees on elevated blocks or near structures $3,000-$8,000+. Body corporate jobs with multiple trees quoted per project. Free on-site assessment and written quote." },
      { q: "Can you remove trees on elevated Mount Sheridan blocks?", a: "Yes. Many Mount Sheridan properties are on sloped or elevated terrain. We have experience with hillside tree removal — controlled sectional felling, careful lowering of branches, and working on uneven ground. We plan every job around the specific access and terrain." },
      { q: "Do you handle tree removal for Mount Sheridan body corporates?", a: "Yes. We work with body corporate managers and strata committees throughout Mount Sheridan. We provide written quotes, can attend committee meetings if needed, and schedule work to minimise disruption to residents. Common area trees are one of our regular job types." },
      { q: "Do you remove mango trees in Mount Sheridan?", a: "Yes — mature mango removal is one of our most common jobs in Mount Sheridan. A 30-year-old mango can be 12-15m tall with a massive canopy. We section them down safely, chip all branches, and remove the trunk. Stump grinding available to prevent regrowth." },
      { q: "Do you offer emergency tree removal in Mount Sheridan after storms?", a: "Yes. Mount Sheridan's elevated position makes it vulnerable to storm damage. After cyclones and severe weather, call 0456 190 202 and we'll respond as fast as possible. Fallen trees on houses, cars, and driveways are always prioritised." },
      { q: "Can you advise if a Mount Sheridan tree needs removing?", a: "Yes. We provide free on-site assessments. We'll check the tree's health, structural integrity, proximity to buildings and infrastructure, and advise whether it needs removing, pruning, or monitoring. Not every tree needs to come down — we'll give you an honest recommendation." }
    ]
  },

